Tributes continue to pour in for the late national team player and administrator George 'Nyundo' Omondi. Nyundo, who passed on last week after being ill, was one of the pioneer KCB Lions players and a member of the Kenya team until 1985 when he took part in the Afro-Basket Championship in Abidjan, Ivory Coast. He was also Kenya Basketball Federation (KBF) treasurer and Kenya Premier League (KPL) finance committee chairman. Among those who paid their tributes include former KBF chairmen Joseph Kimani, Morris Aluanga and Agina Wesonga. Others are former KCB FC club vice-chairman Agil Ali, veteran journalist Omulo Okoth, coach George Namake, Pius Omollo, Ronny Owino, Francis Ngunjiri, Patrick Kariuki and Naftali 'Ole' Mwaniki.